PN,40301
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FAn electrician who stabbed a judge's
OL,7,Fdaughter to death in a frenzied rage
OL,8,Fbefore blowing up their home in a gas
OL,9,Fexplosion has been jailed for life.
OL,11,FClifton George, 45, killed his partner
OL,12,FAnnabel Rook, 46, by stabbing her 31
OL,13,Ftimes during a row at their east
OL,14,FLondon home after she had said they
OL,15,Fshould end their 10-year relationship.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FIn the aftermath of the killing,
OL,7,FGeorge started a fire in the basement
OL,8,Fin order to cause a gas canister
OL,9,Fexplosion which ripped through the
OL,10,Fhouse, causing around #400,000 of
OL,11,Fdamage.
OL,13,FAt Snaresbrook Crown Court on Tuesday,
OL,14,FMr Justice Constable KC sentenced
OL,15,FGeorge to life in prison and ordered
OL,16,Fthat he serve at least 23 years in
OL,17,Fprison before becoming eligible for
OL,18,Frelease
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FHe said George had the ability to be
OL,7,Ffriendly and fun, but he had "another
OL,8,Ftroubling side to your character".
OL,10,F"An overwhelming picture has emerged
OL,11,Fof your rage, anger, and volatility",
OL,12,Fsaid the judge, adding that George had
OL,13,Fa "pronounced temper" which could be
OL,14,Fsparked by trivial matters and
OL,15,F"perceived slights".
OL,26,@oD@^OUpD@aO]rD@AOUsD@dO]uD@COUuD@UO]wD@
OL,26,AAOUwD@SO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FTurning to Ms Rook, the judge said a
OL,7,Fpicture of her "shone brightly"
OL,8,Fthrough the testimonies of friends and
OL,9,Ffamily as a person who was "kind,
OL,10,Fattentive, funny, and altruistically
OL,11,Fmotivated, and someone whose instinct
OL,12,Fwas to support, to listen, and to
OL,13,Fimprove the lives of others."
OL,15,FHe rejected George's claim at trial
OL,16,Fthat he had been provoked by Ms Rook
OL,17,Fpushing him, the judge said that would
OL,18,Fhave been "completely out of
OL,19,Fcharacter".
OL,26,@oD@POUoD@_O]qD@\OUuD@]O]zD@KOU{D@JO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,F"She feared you, she feared your
OL,7,Fwrath," he said.
OL,9,F"In your rage and fury, you brutally
OL,10,Fstabbed Annabel to death."
OL,12,FHe added that even after the murder
OL,13,Fand explosion, George "remained
OL,14,Ffixated on your self-absorbed belief
OL,15,Fthat Annabel had betrayed you".
OL,17,FMs Rook's father, retired Old Bailey
OL,18,Fjudge Peter Rook, branded George
OL,19,F"utterly selfish" while her mother
OL,20,FSusanna Rook called him "a wicked,
OL,21,Ftotally narcissistic, damaged person".
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@GO]qD@AOUrD@ZO]uD@WOUwD@^O]{D@
OL,26,AAOU{D@QO]|D@YOU}D@eO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FDelivering a victim impact statement
OL,7,Fin court, Mrs Rook held back tears as
OL,8,Fshe hailed her daughter as
OL,9,F"optimistic, inclusive, and full of
OL,10,Ffun".
OL,12,F"We know we will never be able to come
OL,13,Fto terms with her death, and life
OL,14,Fwithout her is painful and hard to
OL,15,Fbear," she said.
OL,17,F"We do feel Clifton betrayed the trust
OL,18,Fwe placed in him. We welcomed him into
OL,19,Fthe family in every way we could.
OL,26,@qD@AOUrD@DO]tD@AOUwD@FO]yD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,F"Bearing in mind his short fuse,
OL,7,Fparticularly when in drink, we realise
OL,8,Fhis inability to understand and
OL,9,Faddress his own problems means he is,
OL,10,Fwas, and will continue to be a
OL,11,Fdangerous man."
OL,13,FMs Rook's sister Sophie told the
OL,14,Fcourt: "Without Annabel, there is less
OL,15,Fjoy and less hope."
OL,17,FShe said her sister's murder has left
OL,18,Fthe family dealing with the "painful
OL,19,Fquestion of whether we could have done
OL,20,Fmore to help her escape".
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@OO]vD@HOUwD@SO]zD@]OU|D@XO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FGeorge was convicted at trial of
OL,7,Fmurder and he admitted arson over the
OL,8,Fgas explosion he triggered after
OL,9,Fstabbing his partner to death.
OL,11,FHe attempted to claim loss of self-
OL,12,Fcontrol as a partial defence to the
OL,13,Fkilling, but this fell apart thanks to
OL,14,Fevidence of his short fuse, angry
OL,15,Foutbursts at Ms Rook during their
OL,16,Frelationship, and at least one
OL,17,Fincident when he had been violent
OL,18,Ftowards her.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FSophie Rook described the pain of
OL,7,Fhearing George's defence case, saying
OL,8,Fhis attempts to turn the blame on her
OL,9,Ffelt like her sister being attacked
OL,10,Fagain.
OL,12,FMs Rook was the co-founder of social
OL,13,Fenterprise MamaSuze, which helped
OL,14,Frefugee women and children through
OL,15,Fcreative arts workshops.
OL,17,FGeorge killed her on the night of June
OL,18,F16 last year at their home in Dumont
OL,19,FRoad, Stoke Newington, punching and
OL,20,Fthrottling her before arming himself
OL,21,Fwith a kitchen knife.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FGeorge was heard shouting "you lied"
OL,7,Fas he committed the murder, and the
OL,8,Fcourt heard he had flown into a rage
OL,9,Fafter finding out that Ms Rook had
OL,10,Fkept a secret from him which had been
OL,11,Ftold to her in confidence.
OL,13,FIn the aftermath of the murder, George
OL,14,Ftriggered the gas explosion ` likened
OL,15,Fby neighbours to an "mini earthquake"
OL,16,F` which ripped through the property
OL,17,Fand blew off part of the roof.
OL,26,@nD@[OUnD@dO]wD@UOUwD@eO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FProsecutor William Emlyn Jones KC
OL,7,Fsuggested during the trial that the
OL,8,Fblast had been George's attempt to
OL,9,Fdestroy the evidence of the murder, as
OL,10,Fwell as a final "up yours" to the Rook
OL,11,Ffamily.
OL,13,FWhen neighbours came to investigate
OL,14,Fafter the explosion, George was found
OL,15,Flying on the kitchen floor covered in
OL,16,Fblood.
OL,18,FHe admitted that he had "lost it"
OL,19,Fbefore killing Ms Rook and he tried to
OL,20,Fstab himself with a shard of broken
OL,21,Fglass.
OL,26,@rD@QOUrD@ZO]zD@YOUzD@aO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FIn his defence, George insisted he did
OL,7,Fnot have a "short fuse", but friends
OL,8,Fand family of Ms Rook gave evidence of
OL,9,Fhis true character.
OL,11,FMs Rook's best friend, Sian Davin,
OL,12,Ftold jurors she believed George needed
OL,13,Ftherapy for his anger issues and
OL,14,Fdescribed an incident when he pushed
OL,15,FMs Rook against a wall and grabbed her
OL,16,Faround the throat.
OL,26,@oD@LOUoD@WO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G12/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FShe said he had "unreasonable flashing
OL,7,Frage anger" at times, would fat-shame
OL,8,Fand gaslight Ms Rook, and possessed a
OL,9,F"tendency to over-react about small
OL,10,Ftrivial things".
OL,12,FDaniel Varani, a former flatmate of Ms
OL,13,FRook, described the joy of their time
OL,14,Fliving together but said he decided to
OL,15,Fmove out shortly after George moved
OL,16,Fin, because of his "angry outbursts".
OL,26,@nD@QOUoD@KO]qD@AOUrD@OO]xD@TOUxD@dO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G13/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40314
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FThe court heard of an incident in 2024
OL,7,Fwhen George stormed out of Glastonbury
OL,8,FFestival after rowing with one of Ms
OL,9,FRook's friend and then drunkenly
OL,10,Fharanguing his partner.
OL,12,FIn another incident, George had flown
OL,13,Finto a rage when Ms Rook washed his
OL,14,Fchef's knives and left them to drip-
OL,15,Fdry instead of immediately putting
OL,16,Fthem away.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G14/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40315
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FIn 2023, Ms Rook tearfully confided in
OL,7,Fher father about George's short
OL,8,Ftemper, saying living with him was
OL,9,Flike "walking on eggshells" and first
OL,10,Fmentioning the possibility of a break-
OL,11,Fup.
OL,13,FShe told her close friend Catherine
OL,14,FMilne about the relationship
OL,15,Fdifficulties while insisting there had
OL,16,Fbeen no violence and saying: "I don't
OL,17,Fthink he would do that."
OL,26,@qD@FOUqD@[O]xD@^OUyD@XO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G15/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40316
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FMs Davin said her friend had
OL,7,Facknowledged by summer 2024 that the
OL,8,Frelationship was "abusive" and a
OL,9,Fcouple of weeks before her death Ms
OL,10,FRook left her sister a message saying
OL,11,Fthe relationship was "not tenable".
OL,13,F"I fear there will be some more wrath
OL,14,Fto come," she said, in a heartbreaking
OL,15,Fvoicenote which was played during the
OL,16,Ftrial, where she went on to predict
OL,17,Fthey would "get through this and will
OL,18,Fbe stronger for it out the other side".
OL,26,@pD@ROUpD@ZO]sD@VOUsD@bO]uD@AOUvD@IO]yD@
OL,26,ALOUzD@fO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G16/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40317
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FBefore the fatal stabbing, Ms Rook had
OL,7,Ftold George that they should separate
OL,8,Fand he should move out of their home,
OL,9,Fwhich she owned.
OL,11,FBut she had planned to give her
OL,12,Fpartner #50,000 to find a new home,
OL,13,Fand harboured hopes that they would
OL,14,Fcontinue to holiday together in the
OL,15,Ffuture.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G17/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40318
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FGeorge, who had been drinking red wine
OL,7,Fon the night of the murder, had
OL,8,Flearned that he was not legally
OL,9,Fentitled to any share of the property,
OL,10,Fand he started an argument with Ms
OL,11,FRook.
OL,13,F"In the course of that argument he
OL,14,Fpunched her, he then tried to strangle
OL,15,Fher, and then he went to the kitchen
OL,16,Fto get a knife, he came back with the
OL,17,Fknife and he stabbed her to death,"
OL,18,Fsaid Mr Emlyn Jones.
OL,20,F"He lost his temper, and in his rage
OL,21,Fhe murdered Annabel."
OL,26,@uD@AOUyD@cO]|D@AOU}D@UO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G18/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40319
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1781021473
OL,3,CAbusive partner of judge's daughter
OL,4,Cjailed for life for her murder
OL,6,FIn her victim impact statement, Ms
OL,7,FMilne vowed to continue running
OL,8,FMamaSuze as a "great way to keep
OL,9,FAnnabel's legacy alive".
OL,11,FBut she added: "It will never be the
OL,12,Fsame."
OL,14,FMs Rook's murder was "an attack on all
OL,15,Fof us at MamaSuze, and it felt so
OL,16,Fpersonal and abhorrent for a women's
OL,17,Fcommunity leader to be killed like
OL,18,Fthis in her own home."
OL,26,@pD@OOUqD@WO]sD@POUtD@FO]vD@VOUzD@VO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G19/22
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
